          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript employed as a manual for priests in a private or public setting for consultation during rites and ceremonies performed during full and new moon sacrifices. Text outlines procedures (religious law) for the proper performance of atonement rites and may be linked to the performance of rites at the beginning of each cycle (season) of four months (cāturmāsya) of the year, which include purification and ancestor worship.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
